                <p n="1">
                    Hail! Prosperity!
                </p>
                <p n="1-18">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">This is</supplied> the 9th year opposite to the 4th year of king Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ;
                    from <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mutal āka</foreign></supplied> <foreign>aviṭṭam</foreign> obtained on Monday <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiṅkaṭ-kiḻamai</foreign></supplied> in the
                    month of dhanus; for Perumāṉaṭikaḷ of Tirumayilaraṅkam in Iṭaiyyāṟṟu maṅkalam,
                    night and day, for burning <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>erippatāka</foreign></supplied> two <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iraṇṭu</foreign></supplied> perpetual lamps, king
                    <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kō</foreign></supplied> Māṟañcaṭaiyar alias Varaguṇa Mahārājar, the great Lord of the Pāṇḍyans,
                    released and gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>viṭu-tanta</foreign></supplied> into the hand <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaiyyil</foreign></supplied> of Aṇṭanāṭṭu Vēḷāṉ, <gap reason="lost"/> gold <gap reason="lost"/></p>
                
